Top BTech colleges in Telangana include IIT Hyderabad, NIT Warangal, IIIT Hyderabad, Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, University College of Engineering-Osmania University, etc. The top BTech Colleges in Telangana offer BTech courses in 32 different specializations. Some of the top specializations offered by the BTech colleges are Computer Science and Engineering, Electronics and Communication Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Civil Engineering, and so on. The BTech courses are offered on a full-time basis.

IIT Hyderabad is the best BTech college in Telangana, per NIRF ranking 2023. There are over 290 colleges in Telangana that offer the BTech Program to over 2.4 lakh applicants each year. There are a total of 88,199 seats available in the top BTech colleges in Telangana. Out of the 88.199 BTech seats, 64,709 are earmarked for the convenor quota and 23,490 are reserved for the management quota. 

Admission to the 265 Private and 25 Government BTech colleges in Telangana is done based on entrance examinations such as JEE Mains, TS EAMCET, TS ECET, or JEE Advanced. The TS EAMCET round 2 counseling will start on September 28, 2022. Check out: Top Engineering College in Telangana

Top BTech Colleges in Telangana: Rankings

The rankings released by various agencies for the Top BTech colleges in India are done based on several parameters like Research facilities, Teacher to Student ratio, Placement, and so on. According to an editorial piece published by The Hindu, students use the ranking released by NIRF, The Week, or Outlook as guidelines for getting admission to the top colleges in India.

Top BTech Colleges in Telangana with NIRF Ranking 2023

National Institutional Ranking Framework is a method adopted by the Indian government to rank top Education institutions in India based on various parameters. It is under the Ministry of Education. Every year NIRF publishes ranking lists of top Institutions in India for different domains. NIRF is the most trustworthy and popular Ranking agency in India.

NIRF does not rank the top BTech colleges in India, instead, it ranks the top Engineering colleges in India. Tabulated below are some of the top BTech colleges in Telangana as per the NIRF Ranking.

Top BTech Colleges in Telangana with The Times Ranking

The Times is one of the world's most reputed and largest English-language daily newspapers. Every year, Optimal Media Solutions - The Times in partnership with Avance India conducts a survey and releases a list of Top Education Institutions in India for different domains. The Times ranking considers various parameters to rank a college.

As per the Times Ranking, Anurag University-Hyderabad is the best BTech college in Telangana. The Institute offers BE/ BTech courses with more than 12 specializations and has a seat intake of 1560.

  • Anurag University and Vardhaman College of Engineering are the top Engineering colleges in Telangana offering BE/ BTech. They are ranked 29 as per the latest Times ranking.

Top BTech Colleges in Telangana: Return on Investment (ROI)

Return on Investment or ROI shows how profitable it is to pursue a particular course from a particular college. It is the comparison of the fee you invest while studying and the return you get in the form of placement. In the case of popular management and engineering courses, choosing a college or university based on the ROI factor can be very much beneficial. The following is the list of the top Btech colleges in Telangana based on return on Investment.

College/ University Name  Average Annual Fees  Average Placement Package  ROI Rank*
NIT Warangal INR 1,30,000 INR 19.9 LPA 1
IIT Hyderabad INR 2,23,000 INR 27.11 LPA 2
IIIT Hyderabad INR 3,30,000 INR 32.0 LPA 3
IARE Hyderabad  INR 1,10,000 INR 5.50 LPA 4
VNR VJIET Hyderabad INR 1,31,000 INR 5.0 LPA 5

*ROI= {(Average Placement Package)/ (Average Annual Fees)} *100%

Top BTech Colleges in Telangana: Admission Process

Telangana is home to some of India's most prestigious and highly ranked BTech colleges. The state has a total of 207 BTech colleges, out of which 25 are government-run and 180 are privately owned. A majority of the top engineering colleges in Telangana are approved by the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE), and more than 138 BTech colleges are affiliated with JNTU Hyderabad. The chart below provides a clear breakdown of the ratio between private and government-run BTech colleges in Telangana:

Source: Official Survey

Most BTech colleges in Telangana admit students based on entrance exams. Merit-based admissions are rare. To secure admission, one must pass an entrance exam such as JEE Mains, TS ECET, TS EAMCET, etc. Additionally, some top private colleges conduct their own entrance exams like BITSAT and VITEEE. Students who pass the entrance exams should participate in the counseling process and appear for personal interviews..

Indian Institute of Technology, Hyderabad

IIT Hyderabad Admission 2023 is ongoing. IIT Hyderabad BTech 2023 admissions are JEE Advanced score-based. JEE Advanced 2023 admit card is going to be released on May 29 and the exam will be conducted on June 04, 2023, in CBT mode only. Latest Updates: IIT Hyderabad Admissions 2023

IT Hyderabad is conducting its placement drive for the batch 2023 and till now 508 offers were received by the students. IIT Hyderabad highest package stood at INR 65.46 LPA and IIT Hyderabad's average package stood at INR 20.46 LPA. A total of 141 recruiters participated. Students also received 46 international offers.

Top BTech Colleges in Telangana: Entrance Exams

The majority of BTech colleges in Telangana demand a TS EAMCET and JEE Main scorecard for admissions. Other accepted exams at top BTech Colleges in Telangana are AP EAMCET, JEE Advanced, GITAM GAT UGTP, BITSAT, and NPAT.

Top BTech Colleges in Telangana through EAMCET

TS EAMCET 2024 exam date is the second week of May 2024. TSCHE will release TS EAMCET 2024 application form in the first week of March 2024. According to TS EAMCET Cutoff, candidates must score a minimum of 25% i.e., 40 out of 160 in TS EAMCET 2024 to qualify the exam. However, there are no minimum qualifying marks for SC/ST candidates. Check TS EAMCET 2024 Marks vs Rank

Top BTech Colleges in Telangana: FAQ 

Ques. Which college is best for engineering in Telangana?

Ans. IIT Hyderabad is the best Engineering college in Telangana according to the latest NIRF ranking. IIT Hyderabad occupies an all-India rank of 8. The Institute has a composite score of 66.44 out of 100. IIT Hyderabad is followed by NIT Warangal which has an all-India rank of 19. 

Ques. Which college has the best placement in Telangana?

Ans. IIIT Hyderabad offers the best placement among the top engineering colleges in Telangana with an average package of INR 24 LPA. The institute is followed by IIT Hyderabad with an average package of INR 22.07 LPA. 

Ques. What are the fees for BTech in Hyderabad?

Ans. The average fees for pursuing Btech from the Top engineering colleges in Hyderabad range between INR 27,000- INR 300,000 per annum

Ques. Which college has Google placement?

Ans. Among the top BTech Colleges in Telangana, Google offers placement at Warangal and IIT Hyderabad. Google offered the highest package in the history of IIT Hyderabad with a total package of INR 1.2 Crore.

Ques. What BTech branches are available at IIT Hyderabad?

Ans. The following BTech branches available are: 

  • Chemical Engineering
  • Computing and Engineering
  • Electrical and Engineering 
  • Material Science and Metallurgy (MSME)

Ques. What are the minimum requirements for a BTech Degree?

Ans. It is necessary to earn a minimum of 125-130 credits (will vary therein range for every branch) and also fulfill the category-wise credit requirements like core courses, core electives, humanistic discipline electives, etc. Additionally, satisfactory completion of NSS/ NSO activities is mandatory. Further, there exists a minimum residency requirement of 4 years. This suggests that you simply cannot complete the BTech program in but four academic years or eight semesters.

Ques. What percentage of courses/ credits do I even have to require per semester?

Ans. In the mean, one registers for about 18 to twenty credits of coursework per semester. This might vary from student to student and semester to semester. within the first semester, students are expected to require around 16-20 credits (depending on the branch).

Ques. What are the various fields for Research after BTech?

Ans. The various fields for research after BTech are Robotics, wireless communication, speech processing, MT, search engines, computer vision, pattern recognition, databases, data processing, VLSI, embedded systems, and bioinformatics.

Ques. What percentage of engineering seats are available in Telangana?

Ans. This has raised the entire count of engineering seats within the state to 95,235. Out of the entire count, 64,566 seats are going to be offered through the Convener quota and 30,669 are reserved for the management quota.
Ques. Can I get direct admission to IIIT Hyderabad?

Ans. IIIT Hyderabad won't give any direct admission to candidates. you've got to offer JEE mains and a score of good marks in it i.e. 150 or above then only you'll get admission there.

Ques. Is Hostel compulsory at IIIT Hyderabad?

Ans. Yes, IIIT-H is a residential Institute and all students must reside on campus. Separate hostels for boys and girls are available on-campus with basic facilities. Hostels are completely networked with Internet facilities. UG1 students are not provided with network facilities in their hostel rooms.

Ques. Which is better? NIT or IIIT?

Ans. It depends on which IIIT/NIT you're getting consistent with your rank. In terms of placement, faculties, and infrastructure some IIITs are much better than many NITs. Also, the coding culture of IIITs is way better than many NITs. If you're curious about CSE/IT then IIIT-H is the best choice for you.

Ques. Is IIIT a government institute?

Ans. IIIT Hyderabad, IIIT Bhubaneswar, and IIIT Bangalore are state-owned/private institutes that are often mistaken for central govt. institute by the scholars, the remainder of IIITs is govt. This IIIT is the International Institute of Information.

Ques. Which NIT has the simplest placement?

Ans. According to placement stats for 2022–23, these were the simplest NITs placement-wise:

  • NIT Warangal.
  • MNNIT Allahabad.
  • NIT Surathkal.
  • NIT Trichy.
  • NIT Calicut.
  • NIT Kurukshetra.
  • SVNIT Surat.
  • MNIT Jaipur.
